[b]Structure Break Risk [WavesUnchained][/b]

[b]What it does[/b]
Structure Break Risk (SBR) is a forward-looking 0–100 gauge of how close the prevailing trend's structure is to breaking. It is symmetric by design: in an uptrend it scores top-break risk, in a downtrend bottom-break risk. The direction is decided by the active trend, never hardcoded — and it latches through transition zones so risk can build before the trend formally flips. The key idea: risk rises as price approaches the decisive break level and extra evidence stacks up, not only after the break is confirmed.

[b]Five evidence sensors[/b]
[list]
[*][b]Near Break Level[/b] — distance from price to the decisive swing level, in ATR; risk rises on approach
[*][b]Confirmed BOS[/b] — a close beyond the opposite swing level, graded by depth
[*][b]Failed Breakout / SFP[/b] — a sweep of a swing that closes back inside
[*][b]Structure Erosion[/b] — a lower high in an uptrend (or higher low in a downtrend)
[*][b]Pivot Divergence[/b] — a higher price pivot while RSI at the pivot is lower
[/list]
The sensors are weighted into one score — never an all-or-nothing chain — so the gauge escalates as evidence accumulates. A Reason read names the dominant driver so the score explains itself. Pivots provide the swing levels (location reference); the break event itself is the trigger.

[b]Reading it[/b]
The oscillator height is the risk, its colour the implied resolution (red = top-break / bearish, green = bottom-break / bullish) and its saturation the risk level, with an optional heat-column fill. State bands run No Context / Low / Elevated / High / Critical, read as: 0–35 no acute risk, 35–60 watch, 60–80 structure turning critical, 80–100 break very near or confirmed.

[b]Pairs with Trend Persistence Score[/b]
Read the two together: TPS measures how clean the trend is, SBR how close it is to breaking. TPS low + SBR high = an unclean trend that is also breaking (top/bottom risk); TPS high + SBR rising = a strong trend showing its first structural cracks.

[b]Features[/b]
[list]
[*]Symmetric, situation-driven scoring — no hardcoded long/short
[*]Evidence-hold window and adjustable sensor weights, state levels and pivot/range lengths
[*]Optional confirmed-break markers on real break events
[*]Single compact, mobile-friendly info label (risk, state, direction, reason and all five sensor values) plus a debug log on state change
[*]High / Critical / Top-Break / Bottom-Break alerts
[/list]

